<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Sepulchre1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Sepulchre,</orth> subst. (ordinarily <emph>sépulchre,</emph> but <emph>sepúlchre</emph> in <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.196" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 196</bibl>. Not used in prose, except by the ranting Sir Toby in <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.262" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 262</bibl>), a grave, a tomb: <bibl n="shak. ven 622" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 622</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 68.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 68, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lc 46" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 96</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.262" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 262</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.196" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 196</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.236" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 236</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.17" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.5.115" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 115</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 141</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 48</bibl>.
